cards.title: The 108 Righteous Bandits
cards.text: Noon, Boot: Move your dude to the location of another of your Dudes (without booting, and even if booted).

cards.title: Eagle Wardens
cards.text: Noon, Boot: Boot your dude at the Town Square to draw two cards. If that dude has 2 or more influence, draw one additional card. Discard or ace a card in your hand.

cards.title: Benjamin Washington
cards.text: React, Boot: At the start of the game, discard one or more cards from your hand. For each card you discard, one dude gets -2 upkeep (to a minimum of 0) until High Noon. Draw a card.

cards.title: Daomei Wang
cards.text: React: After Daomei Wang comes into play during High Noon, move one of your other dudes to another location (without booting).
cards.flavor: "I'll keep an eye on him, but I am pretty sure he's keeping an eye on me too." -Gang Yi

cards.title: Randall
cards.text: While Randall is at a location with two or more other dudes (any players'), your maximum hand size is increased by one.
cards.flavor: "I'm just a humble spinner of tales."

cards.title: Xiaodan Li
cards.text: Xiaodan does not count toward the number of dudes in your starting posse.
cards.flavor: "It's amazing the places that little guy can get into... and out of." -T'ou Chi Chow

cards.title: Longwei Fu
cards.text: While Longwei is at home, your posse has an extra +1 stud bonus (at any location, even if Longwei is not in the posse).
cards.flavor: "I guess he used to be some big general under the Emperor. Now they don't want anything to do with him. Fits in perfectly with Chow's bunch." -Jonah Essex

cards.title: Natalya
cards.text: At the start of the Upkeep phase, if you have less ghost rock in your stash than each other player, you gain the production of the deed at Natalya's location this turn, and other players do not.
cards.flavor: "My spirit can be put to rest with an offering of... let's say five bucks."

cards.title: Xui Yin Chen
cards.text: Shootout, Boot: All dudes in your posse become studs and get +1 influence.
cards.flavor: "Honey in mouth, dagger in stomach." -Chinese proverb

cards.title: Hamshanks
cards.text: While Hamshanks is unbooted at a location you control, other players cannot choose or affect your dudes at this location with their abilities if they could legally choose to affect Hamshanks instead.

cards.title: Hiram Capatch
cards.text: Each of your other dudes at this and adjacent locations has +1 influence during the Upkeep phase.
cards.flavor: "Just lean back and relax. By the way, have I ever told you about my friend Chow?"

cards.title: Yunxu Jiang
cards.text: While Yunxu is in a shootout at a location you control, each of your other dudes in the posse has +1 bullets and +1 value.

cards.title: Abuelita Espinoza
cards.text: While Abuelita is at a deed you do not own, each of your other dudes has -1 upkeep.
cards.flavor: "Stealing from a child? ¡Que Malo!"

cards.title: Bai Yang Chen
cards.text: While Bai Yang is at another player's home, your maximum hand size is increased by two and Bai Yang has -1 upkeep.
cards.flavor: "If my brother put half the effort into his work as he does into looking powerful, he might actually be of some help." -Xui Yin Chen

cards.title: T'ou Chi Chow
cards.text: If your outfit is , T'ou Chi Chow's cost is reduced by 1 (to a minimum of 0) for each deed you control. Noon/Shootout, Repeat: Boot a deed you control to unboot a dude at that deed or adjacent to it.
cards.flavor: "Gomorra's a town built on greed. I'm here to rebuild it."

cards.title: Butch Deuces
cards.text: React, Boot: At the start of the game, look at the top 5 cards of your deck. You may reveal a Spirit or Attire from those cards to shuffle your play hand into your deck and take those cards into your play hand. Otherwise, return the cards to your deck in the same order.
cards.flavor: "Sometimes you just gotta roll them bones."

cards.title: Mazatl
cards.text: Noon: Move Mazatl to a location where there is a Totem.
cards.flavor: "Our brother from the south has many talents. We have use of them all." -Stephen Seven-Eagles

cards.title: Marcia Ridge
cards.text: While Marcia is in the Town Square and you have more influence there than each other player, you may use Controller abilities on adjacent deeds as if you controlled them.
cards.flavor: "Get used to it, Sheriff. The Wardens are here to stay."

cards.title: Richard Faulkner
cards.flavor: "Where Stephen is from, a boy becomes a man by gathering a feather from a live eagle. Before he was old enough to get it, he saw a group of seven boys go through it and thought it was a matter of quantity. The kid came back three weeks later with seven feathers and a whole lot of cuts and scratches. That's the kind of man we're working with. 'Impossible' isn't in his vocabulary."

cards.title: Lydia Bear-Hands
cards.text: Resolution, Boot: Boot a Spirit on Lydia. One of your dudes gets the Harrowed keyword until the end of the shootout.
cards.flavor: "Those who think the body is easier to heal than the spirit haven't practiced medecine out here."

cards.title: Jackson Trouble
cards.text: React: After Jackson moves to or from an Out of Town location, unboot him.
cards.flavor: "No it's not his real name. Truth is, not much is known about him at all. But he's a legendary tracker." -Wylie Jenks

cards.title: Black Elk
cards.flavor: "He travels the boundaries between worlds, talks with the spirits often. He could probably do with spending a bit more time in this realm, but he brings back some of the best stories." -Laughing Crow

cards.title: Bloody Teeth
cards.flavor: "He'd like you to think he got his name from how vicious and dangerous he is and not from how often he gets punched in the mouth." -Laughing Crow

cards.title: Three-Eyed Hawk
cards.text:
After you attach a Sidekick to Hawk from your hand, gain 1 ghost rock.
Sidekicks attached to Hawk can be aced to cover two casualties.
cards.flavor: "I speak with the creatures of the wild. They won't hurt you, not like people will."

cards.title: Sarah Meoquanee
cards.text: Shootout: If a dude in your posse has 3 or more influence, or if a Spirit is at the shootout location, Sarah joins the posse (moving if necessary) and becomes a stud.
cards.flavor: "The cavalry? You're lookin' at her."

cards.title: Smiling Frog
cards.text: Noon: Discard a card to give Smiling Frog +1 bullets. If the card was a Spirit, he gets +2 bullets instead.
cards.flavor: "Scouting for the Wardens sure beats my last job. I'd face Maze Dragons over those idiotic tourists any day."

cards.title: Laughing Crow
cards.text: Noon: Reveal the top two cards of your deck. You may attach any revealed Spirits, paying all costs. Discard the rest.
cards.flavor: "Medecine is my caw-ling! Get it?"

cards.title: Chief Stephen Seven-Eagles
cards.text: If your outfit is , Chief Stephen's cost is reduced by 1 for each card (any player's) attached to any location(s). Noon, Boot: While at the town square, Chief Stephen is worth 1 control point for each card attached to deeds you control.

cards.title: Nunchucks
cards.text: Can only attach to a dude with Kung Fu. While in a posse, this dude has +1 Kung Fu. React, Boot: If this dude is in a posse, after a player pulls, reduce the pull by this dude's Kung Fu rating.

cards.title: Idol of Tlazolteotl
cards.text: During High Noon, this dude has +2 influence. Noon, Boot: Choose a card that you own and that is attached to a location. Attach it legally to a deed you control.

cards.title: Spirit Guidance
cards.text: Noon Spirit 7, Boot: Discard a card to draw a card. Noon Spirit 10, Boot: If this Shaman is not at your home, draw two cards, then discard two cards.
cards.flavor: "Even the dead love to gossip." -Laughing Crow

cards.title: Spirit Dance
cards.text: Shootout Spirit 10, Boot: A 2-stud Nature Spirit token enters play and joins your posse.
cards.flavor: "Rejoice with the spirits! Though blood be spilled, they will remain by your side!" -Black Elk

cards.title: Spirit Trail
cards.text: This location is adjacent to each other location that has a Spirit Trail attached. Noon Spirit 6, Boot: Move your dude from this location (without booting, and even if booted).

cards.title: Many Speak as One
cards.text: Noon, Spirit 9, Boot: Put a 1-Influence Ancestor Spirit Token in play at this location.
cards.flavor: "Great chiefs of the past, guide me in forging this new path for your peoples." -Chief Seven Eagles

cards.title: The Pack Awakens
cards.text: Token dudes at this location gain the Harrowed keyword. Shootout Spirit 8, Boot: A 2-stud Nature Spirit enters play, booted, and joins your posse.
cards.flavor: Wolf repays loyalty in kind.

cards.title: Shifu Speaks
cards.text: Noon Technique: If successful, your dude has +1 influence and +2 Kung Fu while not at home, and you may discard up to five cards from the top of your deck.
cards.flavor: "Din boo. Now shift to sui boo." -Longwei Fu

cards.title: Zhu's Ferocity
cards.text: Shootout Tao Technique: If successful, this dude gets +1 bullets and an opposing dude gets -1 bullets. Combo if this dude has higer bullets than the opposing dude.

cards.title: Raking Dragons
cards.text: Shootout Tao Technique: If successful, choose a dude. Boot that dude and give them -2 value. Combo if the affected dude has lower value than this dude.

cards.title: Rabbit's Lunar Leap
cards.keywords: Technique • Tao of the Jade Rabbit
cards.text: Shootout Tao Technique: If successful, move this dude into your posse. You may unboot this dude. Combo if your posse does not have more dudes than the opposing posse.

cards.title: Zhu's Reward
cards.text: Shootout Tao Technique, Boot: If successful, all opposing dudes with value lower than this dude's bullets are sent home booted.
cards.flavor: "Zhu's end may lead to great wisdom, but mostly it's just my favorite part." -Longwei Fu

cards.title: Ancestor Spirit
cards.text:
Cannot be included in decks.
Remove this token from the game if it leaves this location, or at the end of the turn.

cards.title: Nature Spirit
cards.text:
Cannot be included in decks.
Remove this token from the game after this shootout.
